1. Statement of the Problem

The post asserts that:
	•	Most alleged quotations about the incomprehensibility of quantum mechanics are fabricated.
	•	Richard Feynman clearly made such a statement, but “as a joke.”
	•	John Wheeler likely did not.
	•	A second-hand Bohr quote exists.
	•	The issue ultimately depends on what “understanding” means.
	•	The mathematics is straightforward; intuitive sense varies with exposure.

This appears sober. It is not.

